<h1>BBC News Online: Mobile Sites &amp; Apps/Handheld Devices/News</h1>
 
<p>Visitors to <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/">BBC News Online</a> get the stories they want no matter where they are and what device they are using. From breaking news to in-depth analysis, features, interactive graphics and videos, all of our content is made with mobile in mind.</p>
 
<h2>Fast and responsive</h2>
 
<img src="img/mobile/1.jpg" />
 
<p>The past year has continued to see an ever-greater share of our audience access the site through mobiles and tablets, which now account for more than half of all visits.</p>
 
<p>Nowhere is the importance of handheld devices clearer than around big breaking stories, particularly when the news comes out of office hours.</p>
 
<p>When results were announced in the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/events/scotland-decides">Scottish independence referendum</a> traffic peaked early in the morning. Between 6am and 7am 75% of the audience was on mobile and tablet.</p>
 
<p>All of our content is optimised for mobiles, so users were able to access the full results service - including our live page, graphics and video reports. In all, 9.9m smartphone users and 3.6m tablet users visited the site - with a total of 23.3m across all devices.</p>
 
<p>The busiest day in the website's history came on 7 April, when news of the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-26931337">death of Peaches Geldof</a> broke during the evening rush hour.  Of the 23.5m visitors to the site that day, a record 10.4m were on mobile with a further 3.3m on tablet.</p>
 
<p>Other big stories included the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28749702">death of Robin Williams</a>, with a combined audience of 11.5m on mobile and tablet.</p>
 
<p>Away from breaking stories, we ensure that visitors on handheld devices get the best possible experience, no matter what the content.</p>
 
<p>Mobile-friendly formats included the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-27161671">Body Clock</a> project, which used animations, video and a quiz to allow users to discover whether they are a lark, or an owl - and what that means.</p>
 
