The coming year will see further improvements, with a new app due to launch in January offering greater personalisation based on linked data.</p>
 
<h2>A trusted source</h2>
 
<img src="img/mobile/2.jpg" />
 
<p>Underpinning the success of BBC News Online on mobile is its access to journalists around the world and the unparalleled coverage of developing stories that brings.</p>

<p>Speed is key on fast developing stories, with our breaking news tool sending out mobile, web, push, Twitter, SMS and email alerts at the push of a button.</p>

<p>Quick and frequent updates follow, with news stories complemented by video, multimedia live pages, graphics, first-hand accounts and analysis, plus tweets from accounts including @BBCBreaking, which has 12.4m followers.</p>

<p>As stories develop we continue to tell them in a compelling and accessible way, with authoritative reporting despite sometimes difficult conditions.</p>

<p>Our <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-28754546">in-depth coverage of the Ebola outbreak</a> has been led by frequent on-the-ground reports from affected areas, including those from a <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-29888067">village on the frontline</a> in Sierra Leone and a <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-28544605">treatment centre</a> in Guinea.</p>

<p>These were enhanced by a determination to set the disease in context, including pieces on <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-30199004">how the outbreak began</a> and <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-29518703">how to stay safe</a>.</p>
 
<p>On WhatsApp we offered a “lifeline” Ebola information service which is particularly popular in affected areas.</p>
 
<p>The BBC's determination to tell the stories that matter was further demonstrated by bespoke series including <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-17258397">Syria's War</a> - a focus on the country's ongoing crisis. Content included the story of <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-29653526">Syria's disappeared</a> and reports from inside <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-30049219">Aleppo</a> and <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-30011154">Damascus</a>.</p>
 
<p>This year we have also offered in-depth looks at the lives of women worldwide through the series <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-24371433">100 Women</a>, while the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-25683135">Freedom</a> series examined what the word means to people.</p>
 
<p>Two indexes - <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/the_reporters">The Reporters</a> and <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/explainers">Explainers</a> - were launched to offer a prominent home to the best of our analysis and guides. Among these is the 60-second series of video explainers on topics ranging from the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-29996475">Rosetta mission</a> to <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-29727311">Sweden's submarine hunt</a>.</p>

<p>Another popular development has been <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs/trending/">BBC Trending</a>, about what is being shared on the internet and why. Reports - online, radio and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/bbctrending">YouTube</a> - included the revelation that <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-30057401">Syrian 'hero boy'</a> footage had been faked by a Norwegian film crew.</p>
 
<h2>Social media and the BBC</h2>

<img src="img/mobile/3.jpg" />

<p>BBC News has had a very successful year on social media, with a dramatic increase in the number of fans for the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/bbcnews">BBC News Facebook page</a>, up 9.5m to more than 12.8m.</p>
 
<p>The number of Twitter followers for <a href="https://twitter.com/BBCBreaking">@BBCBreaking</a> rose four million to 12.4m.</p>
 
<p>The <a href="http://instagram.com/bbcnews/">BBC News Instagram Channel</a> attracted 100,000 followers with its daily 15-second news reports, while the BBC has 400,000 followers on Line and 75,000 on <a href="https://vine.co/bbcworld">Vine</a>.</p>
 
<p>At the heart of this success was a determination to bring engaging and original content to our followers no matter platform they use.</p>
 
<p>Examples include a daily infographic #BBCGoFigure, which has proved popular on Twitter, Facebook, Instagram and <a href="http://uk.pinterest.com/bbcnews/bbc-go-figure/">Pinterest</a>.</p>
 
<p>In the US, the <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-28843888">Pop Up</a> series of video reports saw the BBC's first mobile bureau set up - its team travelling to a new town each month to engage with community residents and tell their stories.</p>

